options.prioritizeChunkUpdates.none.tool: §5Nearby chunks are compiled in parallel threads. This may result in brief visual holes when blocks are destroyed.
§5Some actions within a chunk will recompile the chunk immediately. This includes block placing & destroying.
options.prioritizeChunkUpdates.nearby.to: §5Nearby chunks are always compiled immediately. This may impact game performance when blocks are placed or destroyed.
options.graphics.fabulous.tooltip:
§5%s graphics uses screen shaders for drawing weather, clouds, and particles behind translucent blocks and water.
This may severely impact performance for portable devices and 4K displays.
options.graphics.fancy.tooltip:
§5Fancy graphics balances performance and quality for the majority of machines.
Weather, clouds, and particles may not appear behind translucent blocks or water.
options.graphics.fast.tooltip:
§5Fast graphics reduces the amount of visible rain and snow.
Transparency effects are disabled for various blocks such as leaves.
options.graphics.warning.title: §5Graphics Device Unsupported
options.graphics.warning.message:
§5Your graphics device is detected as unsupported for the %s graphics option.

You may ignore this and continue, however support will not be provided for your device if you choose to use %s graphics.
